inn1.comm: lively start, Anderson landing it on a length outside off, finding some away movement and carry, Watson plays and misses
Watson is away, in quiet fashion, similar delivery to the last but this time Watson got a thickish outside edge which ran to point for a single
Tim Paine, who could do with some runs ahead of his Test debut later in the summer, begins with a very certain leave outside off
Anderson managing to hold his off-stump line well for now, Paine hops into a tight back-foot defence
this is turning into a good first over, Paine defending a touch uneasily off the back foot
good finish from Anderson! Chopped Paine in two, pitching on a length, jagging back down the slope and beating Paine on the inside edge
decent start for the bowler, nothing fancy, just landing it on a good length, finding a touch of movement, Watson half plays and misses
touch fuller this time, Watson thrusts his front leg out and leaves it well alone
Watson seems content to get his eye on for a while, leaving the ball outside off stump
good stuff here from Bresnan, holding in just back of a length outside off stump, not giving Watson a chance to unfurl his booming drive, and it's left alone
another off-stump ball, Watson gets half forward and defends with an outside edge
beaten! Excellent delivery to end a probing over, angling in from wide of the crease, pitching on a length and jagging away past the outside edge
Anderson continues the good work, moving the ball into Paine once more, the batsman left it on length, which I always like to see
Paine is away, in unspectacular fashion, getting into line and skewing an inside edge off his back-foot defence for a single behind square on the leg side
that's better! Watson has seen enough of this back-of-a-length tactic and pulls off the front foot, powering it through midwicket for four
and again! Didn't time it perfectly but it does not matter at all, short from Anderson, Watson latches on to the pull shot for a second boundary

well, what happened here!? It was a zipping shortish ball around off stump, Watson tried to cut but extra bounce cramped him for room there was a sound as it passed the bat, massive appeal from England but Aleem Dar rules not out
quieter finish to the over, outside off once more and Watson leaves alone
good stuff from Bresnan, finding a bit of nibble off the pitch, this time into Paine, who shoulders arms
this time it moves away and beats Paine on the outside edge
Bresnan continues to hold a decent off-stump line, and there is not much Paine seems able to do, just defending, pressure building on him again
oh dear, that looked a touch desperate, Paine gave himself room outside leg, aimed a big scythe over cover but swished only at thin air
another play and miss outside off, but this was a touch too wide for the umpire's liking
this time Paine connects, quietly defending
Paine keeps the strike, unfortunately for Australia, dabbing a single to mid on
nicely played by Paine there, Anderson went full, testing to see if there is any swing about - there isn't - Paine leant it past mid on for three
Anderson drags his length back, which is wise against Watson, and it's left alone
good from Anderson here, jagging it down the slope and cramping Watson as he tries to defend
this time it's outside off and Watson lets it go once again
very solid defence from Watson, thrusting forward and full-facing it to cover
Anderson working up some decent pace here, and once again moves it back into the batsman, who leaves alone and watches alarmed as it climbs back over off stump
Bresnan continues to probe around off stump, Paine leaves alone
this time it's played a touch more certainly as he defends
Paine is really struggling here, beaten outside off stump and he looks very tentative, leaning forward to defend but missing
another slightly nervy defence, Paine leans half forward and it runs off the outer half of the bat
Paine leans forward into a forward defence and it goes gently into the off side
Paine once again nicks the strike, guiding it neatly to third man for one
close there, almost squeezed through, Paine was defending with no foot movement and it got an inside edge down to fine leg for one
Watson leaves outside off, with a touch of flourish it must be said, holding the pose for a while
well, this really is English one-day cricket, hard graft at the top of the order, Watson leaves once more from a ball the came back at him
Watson plays at this, but it's a forward defence
good run here, Australia probably need a few more of these, Watson dabs it into the leg side and scampers through for one
ooh, pressure almost doing for Paine there, he skipped down the wicket, Anderson dropped it short, Paine pulled and found a top-edge that looped one-bounce to fine leg
that will do his confidence some good, not perfectly timed, but Paine gets an overpitched ball from Bresnan, and drives through the covers for four
good response from Bresnan, drags the length back a fraction and Paine plays and misses outside off
this time Paine connects, defending quietly on off stump
poor shot this, real nothing shot, Paine aimed an open-faced glide to third man, with no foot movement and is beaten
Paine forward and defending once again
no strike-stealing single here, Paine instead blocks off the front foot
well, new bowler, same result, outside off stump and left alone
shot! Watson made this look so easy, it was a fraction short and in a flash he thwacked it through midwicket
this time Broad reverts to a better line outside off, and Watson plays at this, which suggests a change of mentality, but it's only a defence
fuller and Watson rocks forward into a full-blooded forward defence
Broad strikes! Watson departs and after all the hard work he's put in, this is a bit of a soft dismissal. Short ball on about off stump, Watson cracked a pull shot straight to mid on.
Broad goes full first up, almost yorker length and dug out by Ponting
nicely done by Paine, easing a fullish ball through midwicket for a swiftly-run three
Ponting defends his first ball from Bresnan easily enough, getting forward with a full face
outside off stump and Ponting plays his big leave
outside off stump again and Ponting thrusts his foot out and leaves alone with a flourish
this time it's angled down the leg side, Ponting aimed the pull shot but couldn't get anything on it
ooh, beaten! Lovely ball that, movement away from the bat and some extra bounce, climbs past Ponting's outside edge
left alone outside off to finish the Powerplay. Good summary of it really.
good length outside off, climbing through to the keeper. No stroke
fuller and attacking the top of off. Dabbed into the leg side and they scamper through
overpitched a fraction outside off, pushed into the covers and they turn down a risky two. Ponting glares at Paine for a hesitant call
back and across, and defended to midwicket
oops, that's a bit misdirected. Wa-ay down the leg side
outside off this time, Ponting unfurls his best Test-match leave-alone to usher that one through. Bat high, front knee bent, you know the drill
cracking strike to finish the over, just enough width and Ponting leathers it off the back foot, through the covers. No stopping that
drawn forward, and deflected down to gully. Good line
chipped in the air and through the gap at midwicket. A touch lucky, maybe? I suppose he found the gap well enough
punched into the covers off the back foot this time
Bresnan goes wide of the crease and draws a straight-batted defence in front of middle and off
sublime. There's no stopping that. Eases into a flicked on-drive as Bresnan strays a touch. He's ticking now
what on earth was that? A filthy flat-footed mow, just as I was singing his stylish praises. No contact, and for Ponting's sake, that's just as well
tucked off the hip to midwicket
fuller and straighter, Ponting defends
worked to midwicket but can't pick the gap
slower ball, tossed up a touch, met on the half-volley and eased to mid-on
jabbed to gully
pushed firmly into the covers, can't beat the field
outside off, a hint of late movement, no stroke offered
flicked off the pads, down to fine leg
tight line from Anderson, Ponting bides his time
tucked up by a hint of movement back off the track.
swished off the pads, French-cricket style. Effective enough
attempted late steer through point, but can't get the angle. Good over for England's purposes
clipped up and out to square leg.
snorter! That one utterly flew off a good length. Paine whips his gloves, neck, bat, everything, inside the line
another short ball, Paine turns turtle, as Ponting pats his bat in approval
stands tall this time to defend from back in the crease
more aggression from Broad. A feisty over
pushed back onto the stumps, and England have strung together a good sequence of overs to stifle Australia's intent for the moment
speared into the pads, flicked out to square leg
zips off the deck, raps the pads, always going high, but a lively delivery all the same
poked back to the bowler, good areas Jimmy
worked out to deep midwicket, Bell jogs round to field.
drawn forward on a good length, pushed into the covers
down the track from Ponting, to marvellous effect. That fairly whistled back past the bowler, all along the ground. Top batting
pushed out to cover
this one climbs and zips back into the batsman. Good bowling
testing times for Paine. The back-of-a-length tactics are cramping his style
short again and pulled, without much conviction. Fine leg fields on the bounce
solidly forward, pushed up to cover

short again, and that's the big breakthrough that England needed! An attempted pull, but Ponting muffs his signature stroke, and lobs a simple chance almost off the back of his bat, straight through to Kieswetter!
solidly forward, punched to cover
good length, a fraction too wide, but left safely alone
over-pitched, and eased through the covers. That's a calm stroke, and mightily effective
too short, and pulled urgently, but without much timing to square leg
angled into the pads, worked square once again
a hint of width, and jabbed to third man
up onto the toes, and tucked to midwicket
banged into the track, slightly back of a length, nurdled to third man
whoops, Collingwood nutmegs himself at point, and gifts an extra run. A rare lapse
dabbed down to third man
banged in short, and smacked hard through backward square. In the air, but excellently placesd
makes room outside off, but an ambitious wipe doesn't quite come off
gives himself room by backing away to leg, but a well-timed drive picks out mid-off
short, and that one appears to chase the batsman as he withdraws his bat. Does well in the end
pitched up to the toes, clipped coolly to midwicket
straightens a touch from leg to off. Well watched, and defended on the line of middle
jabbed down through gully with an open face
quick single to midwicket. Australia keep ticking over
banged in short, no stroke offered there
short again, climbing and following Paine as he attempted a steer to third man. Nearly got in a massive tangle there
clever bowling. The slower ball, juicily served up on a full length outside off. Paine's eyes light up, and he all but chops onto his stumps
forward and defended again to cover
that's a grim shot from Paine. Short, but not terrifyingly so. He completely averts his gaze and splices a leading edge into space in the gully. Lucky to survive
banged in short again, White hops into a clip off the toes
defended down into the crease.
open-faced steer to third man
defended on the line of off stump
worked off the toes, out to midwicket
short again, and Paine pulls without conviction. Midwicket fields
up onto the toes, but there's no width to work with. Point tidies up an attempted late cut. And Paine is visible frustrated.
good length, outside off. Pushed back to the bowler
familiarly wide of the crease. White can't work with the angle
blocked into the off side
tucked off the pads
tossed up, and swished to midwicket
extravagently wide of the return crease - that's encroaching on no-ball territory. But the upshot is a very tidy over indeed
poked out to cover
driven off the back foot, Wright stoops in his followthrough, and intercepts
tidy line and length, nothing to work with there
flicked off the toes to backward square
Paine decides to up the ante. Short again, but this time he climbs into a premeditated tennis smash. Good aggression, trying to break the shackles
worked out to the off side, White snaffles the strike
massive appeal as White misses an attempted sweep. Outside the line
jabbed into the off side
reverse sweep and excellently executed
wide of the crease once again, the angle is effective
punched into the covers and they amble a single
Wright bustles up another on off stump, carefully pushed in to the off side
short ball here, White whirls away a pull shot that flies off the top edge, sailing comfortably into a gap at fine leg for four
altogether more careful here, fully behind a defensive block
decent line from Wright, not much movement now for him though, and it's pushed to deep point
played with very soft hands by Paine, defending and it came off the outside edge, ran down to third man where Broad slides well to field, and somehow keep it to two, should have been a third there
Paine opens the face and guides it more certainly down to third man again
that'll do nicely for Paine, neat cut shot, off the back foot, beating short third man and running away for four to bring up  a fifty
he looks a much happier character now, but will need to accelerate as the innings goes on, this is useful, working it to midwicket for one
White aims a big heave-ho at Yardy, but clumps nothing but thin air as Yardy fired it through
nothing expansive here, just quiet defence
something verging on delicacy from White here, dabbing to point for one
Paine inside-edges a defensive shot to end the over
starts tidily, bit of flight, White forward and blocking

Swann does it again! The first-over demon strikes! White was looking to give himself room, Swann threw it wider and slower and White ended up dragging it without any timing down to Yardy, in from the long off boundary
beaten! Just went on with the arm and sneaked past the outside edge
well, Paine didn't quite pull this off, but the reverse-sweep gets a single off the bottom edge
Marsh defends his first ball quietly enough, but there is a slip in place
well, this is why there is a slip! Pitches and rips past the left hander's edge. Top bowling
Yardy building good pressure with his darts, Paine defending hurriedly off the back foot
this time Paine is forward, but there is still no run
Paine tries to manufacture something, giving himself some room, but before he can do anything the ball is on him and he can't time it
this time it's a more conventional dot ball, blocked away
better from Paine, skipping down the wicket and milking a single down to long on
not sure how they didn't take a single here, Marsh pushed it into a gap at point and set off, Paine couldn't quite decide what to do and eventually sent Marsh back
nicely done from Swann, slow and flighted and Paine is forward and defending
Paine can't quite work the singles here, instead picking midwicket with a leg-side clip

oh dear, this is ugly. Pain gets in a horrible tangle, aiming an expansive reverse-sweep to a flighted ball outside off, it pitched and turned back, spinning into a flurry of gloves and bat and cannoning on to the stumps
defends his first ball carefully enough, looking busy as ever
Hussey forward again, patting towards cover
Hussey is off, cutting towards point and bustling through for a single
Yardy over the wicket, spearing this into Hussey, who happily works it to point for a single
Marsh turns this with the angle round the corner for a single
Australia already look more busy with Hussey at the crease, working another single to square leg
Yardy back round the wicket, makes little difference though as Marsh clips him usefully through midwicket for a single
nicely done by Hussey, dropping a forward defence into the off side and scampering through for a single
dot ball to finish as Marsh taps it down to the bowler
Swann might have got away with this, touch short and wide, but Hussey picks out point
this time Hussey gets a single, working it in front of point for a single
Marsh leans into a forward defensive shot
quietly defended once more
Marsh stretches forward and leans a full-faced defensive to the covers
oops, a single here for Marsh, but not how he intended, getting a leading edge into the covers as he tried to turn it into the leg side
wow, this is slow, an off-cutter I suppose, Marsh taps it back to the bowler
possibly even slower, but accurate and Marsh collects a very easy single, pushing into the covers
with the field set deep this should be middle-over milking, and Hussey does exactly that, chipping it through square leg for one
Marsh this time knocks it into a gap at square leg for another gentle single
on and around off stump, Hussey pushes towards extra cover and helps himself to a single
slightly fuller, Marsh blocks firmly to cover
shouldn't have been a single there, pushed to mid on for one
no single here, just full-faced to short-extra cover
this time Marsh does collect the single, pushing it to point
another single, nicely pushed for a single towards cover
Marsh works it into the leg side and collects one
another single, very simple stuff, worked into the leg side
starts very tidily, on a length on off stump and defended
back of a length this time, Hussey hops into a defensive block, thought about stealing a single, but it's not there
Bresnan has bowled very well today, and finds some away movement off the pitch, zipping past Hussey's outside edge
touch shorter, Hussey back and pulling in a flash, doesn't really time it perfectly but an easy single to deep midwicket
help-your-self single here, England just allowing these two to set a platform, Marsh dabs into space at midwicket and collects one
back of a length this time, Hussey hurries into a back-foot block
confidently played by Marsh, getting down on one knee and sweeping firmly, some good running allows three, much to Swann's disgust
good stuff here, nicely bowled, flighted and drifting, Hussey's drive was crisp, and Collingwood's fielding at short extra sharp
bit of shout here from Swann as Hussey defends with bat and pad
Hussey tries to work this round the corner and can't
this time the single is earned, pushing past the bowler for one
seemed very simple there for Marsh, leant forward, allowed the ball to hit the bat, and ran a single
Bresnan continues to probe around off stump, Marsh can do nothing but defend
bit short from Bresnan, in fact, very shot, and wide enough for the umpire to give it a wide
back on a decent length and line, Marsh bunts it into the leg side and collects a single
lucky that for Hussey, he skipped down the wicket, Bresnan banged it in short, so Hussey delicately helped a pull shot in the air, one-bounce to deep midwicket
Marsh this time pulls, with better timing, but for only a single to midwicket
Hussey collects a couple, chopping into the leg side
cut away for a strike-stealing single
Hussey collects another single, pushing towards long on
nothing here for Marsh as he blocks back to the bowler
Marsh on the sweep, he plays the shot well, firmly down to fine leg
Hussey plays this from the crease, into point and gets a single
well, single eventually, Marsh pushed it to point, didn't want a single, Hussey had come a long way down but Swann missed the throw and they collected one
another single to finish, still quite quiet from Australia
bustles in and dishes up a half-tracker which Hussey pulls firmly in front of midwicket for a couple
nicely done by Hussey, working it with soft hands towards square leg, gently enough to collect a couple
busy is what Hussey always is, and here he pushes to mid off and runs through for a single
Marsh is not quite as fluent at working singles and picks out  point with his back-foot block
touch short from Wright but Marsh cuts straight to point again
well, good second half to the over from Wright, Marsh fails to get a leg-side work away
Hussey begins the Powerplay with a crisp drive, so perfectly straight that it cannoned into the stumps at the bowler's end and ran away for a couple
close here, Hussey pushed to extra cover and ran, Collingwood's throw missed the stumps
Broad might be a touch fortunate here, it was down the leg side and but Marsh couldn't quite work it fine for four, instead collecting a couple to fine leg
short ball here, Marsh aims a big pull shot, but misses
that'll do for Marsh, shot ball finds the glove, but it loops over Kieswetter for four
bang! He got all of that one though! Short and the pull shot was nailed over midwicket, scattering the crowd
good delivery, yorker length, squeezed back past the bowler
misdirected, and that's a poor follow-up. Leg-side full-toss, helped through the gap
bad bowling again from Anderson, but Marsh cashes in to full effect. On the pads, tucked fine
dug out full, into the leg-side
chipped out to square leg, the runs are flowing nicely now
width outside off stump, driven into the gap at cover
that's awful. Misses the cut strip
clunked out to deep point
this is well outside off stump again, Hussey bunts a single to point
good bowling from Broad, much better, full and straight, Marsh blocked it back to the bowler
lovely shot, top stuff. Marsh took a single step forward, eased his arms through the line and pinged the ball straighter over the bowler's head for six
four more! Marsh is playing a blinder, it was full outside off and he sliced it past point for another boundary
oh dear, with that field looping outside off stump doesn't make sense, Hussey drives powerfully past cover for four
good ball this, much better, quicker and angling in, clipped the pad first and Swann appealed, not out but replays suggest it was very close
Marsh up the wicket, pushes into the off side and collects one
very nicely done from Hussey, feathered into the midwicket area, softly enough for two
this time it's a single, dabbed behind square on the off side
another single to finish up, tapped into space behind point
good from Anderson, full, straight and defended
fifty for Marsh, and how well he's played. First game back and he's picked up his seventh ODI fifty off 45 balls, clipping to deep midwicket
can't bowl there, down the leg side and an extra run and extra ball
that's better, full and drilled to mid off for a swift single
nicely done from Anderson, he's landed the yorkers well this over, dug out by Marsh
oops, he hasn't landed that yorker at all! Full toss and Marsh slapped it cleanly, over long on for six
yorker again here, and Marsh jabs a single down the ground
Swann lands this short and it's cut to deep point for one
Marsh waits on the crease, pushes quietly into the off side and takes one
nothing here for Hussey, timing it too well to extra cover
Hussey on the sweep and playing it well down to midwicket

gone this time, Swann does the trick. Marsh tried to smash this inside-out over deep cover, Swann threw it wider and Marsh couldn't get the distance, Morgan ran around from long off to take the catch. Brings the end to an excellent innings
Hussey drops by his feet into the off side and scampers through for one
this is not very good though, fine leg up and Bresnan goes full on leg stump, Hussey flicks it round the corner for four
this time it's a better length and Hussey clips through midwicket for a single
Bresnan angles it in from wide of the crease, Smith works it to square leg and it's another single
Bresnan is very lucky to get away with this, full toss well outside off, should have been four, but Hussey picked out deep point
Smith is shuffling around the crease and Bresnan aims it down the leg side, Smith plays it gently enough to run two
touch shorter and guided to short third man for a swift single
Anderson's return is greeted with with a heave that was mistimed to midwicket
fired down the leg side, Hussey clips it through to fine leg to bring up his run-a-ball fifty
Smith hasn't quite found his range yet, clearing his front leg and aiming a big drive, but mistiming to mid off
repeats the shot but this time plays it perfectly, timing it sweetly through extra cover for four
again Smith hurls is front leg out the way, but this time goes leg side for a single
Hussey is a dangerous man to finish the innings, really, and here he's picked up a full ball and deposited it miles over midwicket for six!
Smith again aims his inside-out shot, but finds mid off
well, Hussey's bat has exploded! He jabbed it out with the toe end and a massive chunk snapped off
it's not all that pretty from Smith, but very effective, he squats down low and tennis-swishes a slog to mid on
Hussey looking for another big leg-side pick-up, but it's a touch too short so he can only find a single to deep long on
Smith is an awkward fellow to bowl at, and here he's connected very firmly with a reverse pull
don't bowl there, not to Hussey, not now! Full toss on leg stump, Hussey smashes it over midwicket for six more
for all his shuffling and awkward positions that Smith gets into, he does seem a very natural timer, after a flurry of movement he guides this sweetly to deep cover
talking about good timing, how about this! Hussey gives himself a fraction of room and carefully eases a drive over cover for four
brilliant batting, really top stuff, Hussey clips it into a gap at square leg for four more. Anderson really suffering here
much better from Anderson, landing the yorker that Hussey digs out
full toss outside off but Smith had decided to go leg-side quite early, so can't quite time it as it heads down to midwicket
startling stuff from Hussey, gets down on one knee and dinks it to fine leg for another boundary
some joy here for England, Smith forehand-slaps a short ball but straight down to Anderson at long off
very good running from Hussey, how he's collected two I don't know, he drilled it down the ground and scampered two
gone this time! Broad gets another, Hussey slicing a drive down to long off, but it has been a superb innings, completely flipped this game on its head
well, Hopes has done this brilliantly, touch short and a touch wide, but the upper cut has flown for six over deep cover
Hopes is playing a two-ball blinder! Slower ball bouncer and he waited and waited before slamming it wide of Anderson at long on for four
two more to finish and what an end that has been for Australia. 130 has come from the last 11 overs

inn2.comm: Tait starts with a loosener... that spits up savagely off a length outside off at more than 90mph. Strauss drops the hands and gets out of the way of that thunderbolt
very quick again, but misdirected down the leg side this time and called wide
Strauss didn't quite pick this one up, but he takes it on the thigh pad and Kieswetter calls him through for a quick single
absolute gem from Tait! Sharp swing away from the bat, late and at high pace. Kieswetter pushes at it, but that was too good to even get an edge on
beaten again! Slightly fuller this time, but the swing is there again and the ball zips past the outside edge
back of a length this time, Kieswetter gets into some difficulty as he fends to leg, the ball pops up but falls safely
full and swinging, but Strauss presents the full face of the bat to defend
good start, outside off and there's a touch of swing back in to Kieswetter, though it's wide enough to leave alone
tapped defensively back down the wicket off the back foot
too straight, and the swing in to the right-hander takes it towards leg stump. Kieswetter nudges to midwicket and they set off immediately
short and wide outside off, you'd back Strauss to cash in on those every time but some extra bounce and movement away from him means the ball loops past the edge. Too far outside off, that's a wide
big swing from Bollinger! Strauss is drawn forward into an optimistic drive but massive, hooping movement away from him means he misses by a good few inches
he's expecting it to move now, and as Bollinger sends one down on a length outside off Strauss just pulls the bat inside the line
beaten on the outside edge! In the channel outside off, close enough that Strauss had to play this time, but the movement takes the ball past the edge.
full, fast and swinging, but Kieswetter drives nicely to mid-off. Beaten for pace though, he only moved forward after the shot had already been played
banged in short, ball hits bat as Kieswetter tries to hook but luckily for him it loops safely behind square leg
full again, punched to cover
nicely played by Kieswetter, the ball shaped away from him off a length but he got on top of it for a single to third man
Strauss shuffles right across to off stump and clips Tait down to fine leg. The pace on the ball means the fielder has to pull out the dive to cut it off
feisty! Well-directed bouncer on middle and off, Strauss buckles the knees to get underneath it. Phew! That's nasty
Kieswetter has a huge swipe to the first ball, which is full outside off, and misses completely
and again! Same ball, same shot, and the result is identical: he hit's nought but fresh air
now he's hit one! Middles a drive, but straight to cover. Sharp fielding there, it was really well struck
squirted defensively to gully off the front foot
after swinging a couple away from the bat, he gets one to jag in off the seam. Kieswetter is hurried in defence, and the ball shoots off the inner half of the bat to midwicket
solid defensive stroke to backward point. That hit the middle, nice crack of bat on ball
short and sharp from Tait, but he's offered width outside off and Strauss uppercuts down to third man. Such was the pace on the ball, it landed just inside the boundary rope!
slower ball, but slips out a full toss outside off and Strauss taps to mid-off

clatter! That's the dismissal every fast bowler wants to see! Tait fires one in on a length, gets some nice shape in to the left-hander to beat his defensive poke and smash into the top of the off stump. That's a real statement: the stump cartwheels out of the ground. First strike for Australia
cuts him in half! I don't think Yardy even saw that, it was right through him before he could even get the bat down. Paine is done by the speed too, and that runs down to fine leg!
speared down the leg side, that's a wide. So Yardy will have to face up to that delivery again...

nope. I don't know what the thinking was sending Yardy in to face Tait, but it really hasn't worked. Tait fires one in fuller and Yardy simply leaves it - I don't think he quite picked the ball up - and the ball smashes into the stumps. There was a slight deflection off the pad, but that was full and straight. Tait strikes again!
woah! Full and fast, Colly jams the bat down just in time to keep the ball out, and sends the ball into the gap on the leg side
full and wide outside off, swinging away and left alone by Collingwood
Collingwood pushes leaden-footed at a length delivery outside off and is well beaten
and again, Harris shapes the ball away to beat the edge of Collingwood's prod. To the batsman's credit, he didn't push at the ball, just played the line
too straight from Harris, and Collingwood nurdles one right out of the middle down to the midwicket boundary. Long boundary there, so a tough chase for the fielder, who does eventually haul it in
quick yorker from Harris, Kieswetter does well to keep it out
banged in outside off, Kieswetter whips his bat out of the way and leaves well alone
on a length, but just too straight and Collingwood goes back and across, very deep in the crease, to work the ball away behind square on the leg side
even at Tait's pace, you can't afford to dish up a delivery like that. Ful and wide, and slapped past backward point for four
pulled infront of square for six! That was anything but a nurdle, Tait drops short and Collingwood just rocks back and scythes through the line to send the ball sailing over the boundary
fuller this time, and the ball is met with the full face of the bat in a defensive stroke
Collingwood shuffles across to off as Tait hurls one down the leg side - that's a wide
full and straight, pushed to mid on
inside edge squirts just past the stumps and straight to the man at short fine leg! That was mighty close, but no harm done in the end
full and punched firmly into the covers
just back of a length on off stump, Kieswetter gets on top of the ball and taps to point. Played it right under his eyes
wonderful shot from Kieswetter, textbook cover drive played on the up through cover. Not a half-volley, but cracked right out of the middle with a high left elbow, and he picks the gap perfectly too
too straight to follow up, and he's flicked down to fine leg where a tumbling stop saves a few runs

leading edge flies to Hussey at extra cover, and Kieswetter departs! Harris had been shaping the ball away from him nicely, and as Kieswetter shaped to clip through midwicket the movement got him into trouble. The ball flew quickly to Hussey's right, but he timed his leap perfectly to snatch it out of mid air. Australia are right on top now!
full to start, and Morgan taps the ball back to Harris
nice start, Bollinger finds some lift outside off to strike the splice of Collingwood's bat
same again, although this time Collingwood was expecting the extra bounce and got up on his toes to play the ball down to point

Bollinger directs one at leg stump and Collingwood rolls his wrists nicely over the ball to send it to the long leg boundary. Nice shot, didn't hit it too hard but got the timing and placement spot on
landing just outside off from over the wicket, and Collingwood leaves alone
and again, he's done his work for the over and so can leave deliveries in the channel outside off without a worry

well, Collingwood wasn't content to just play out the over! He charges down the track to the last ball and aims a massive heave over midwicket. Can't quite connect though, and the ball trickles behind square
driven firmly to cover
little bit of movement away through the air, Collingwood defends a very full ball somewhat awkwardly and the ball rolls into the off side
pushed behind square, but straight to backward point
slipping down towards leg stump, that was there to be hit but Collingwood couldn't lay bat on ball. Perhaps beaten slightly for pace as ball strikes pad
full on off, tapped back to the bowler
pushed just to the right of mid on, giving them opportunity for a quick single
wobbling around outside off, Collingwood is quite happy to leave alone
big appeal from Bollinger as he shapes one back in to the right-hander to strike him on the pad. But it pitched just on leg, and was going way over the top of off, so an optimistic appeal.
pushed across Collingwood, who pulls his bat out of the way and leaves again
full and slightly wider, Collingwood tries a drive but isn't in a great position and the ball skews to cover
back of a length outside off, rising nicely up to about chest height and Morgan leaves alone
now he gets one to jag in to the left-hander off the seam, and the ball is tapped defensively to point with a hop
ball squirts off the inside edge, going to cover as it rebounds off the pad. Morgan wants a run but Collingwood sends him back. A direct hit would've had him there
pulls the length back a touch, and Collingwood pushes to cover
driven on the up, but again straight to cover
full and straight this time, Collingwood tries to nurdle to leg but finds mid-on
hmm, has that kept low? It was on a length outside off and Collingwood aimed to slash it away, but the ball zipped under the bat
tip-and-run to finish the over, as the ball is pushed into the tiniest of gaps at cover and they set off immediately for a single. Nice running
short and quick from Bollinger, not the best directed bouncer, but it beats Collingwood's swivel-pull on its way through to Tim Paine. Umpire lets him know "that's one for the over"
much fuller this time, prodded defensively to midwicket, and they take a quick single
left-hander messes up the radar as he spears one down the leg side
sharp yorker! Morgan is struck on the foot to cries of anguish from the Australian fielders, but that was slipping way down leg
back of a length and straight, Collingwood hops back and across to defend
full, and clipped out to deep midwicket. They briefly consider a second
on a length, and coming in off the seam. Morgan responds with a solid forward defensive, presenting the full face of a straight bat
edged first ball! But that fell just short, and wide, of Watson at slip. Half a chance, but it didn't get to him.
nudged gently off the hip, and they charge through for one as Hopes sprints across after his follow-through
tapped easily to deep mid-on for an ambled single
a touch of movement away off the seam, but Morgan spots it and defends towards cover
Hopes pulls the length back slightly, and again the ball is pushed defensively to cover
pushed too far down leg, that's a wide
tapped out to wide long-on for another easy single
Bollinger bangs one in outside off, Morgan drops his hands and leaves

sharp bouncer! And perfectly directed, Morgan aimed to hook it up and over fine leg but took his eyes off the ball, which took the top edge and touched the shoulder and the bottom of the helmet, flying up and over slip and 'keeper and away for four. Dougie's not pleased, but a moral victory for him
on a length, seaming in and tucked straight to midwicket
pushed just between midwicket and the wide mid-on, and they take a sharp single
driven to mid-off, but not timed
driven to mid-off once again, a slightly better connection but straight to the fielder
this is on a good length and line to welcome Morgan back after the break, defended to cover
lovely shot this, he's been very patient to begin with but now Morgan skips down the wicket, gives himself a bit of room and drives wristily through the covers for four
follows up the boundary with a neat tickle round the corner for two more
this would keep the bowler interested, outside off stump and Morgan just let his hands follow the ball
gone! What a catch! Morgan nailed a pull shot, smashing it flat towards a straightish midwicket, the Marsh in the deep ran round and dived, juggling the ball as he landed to clasp on to the catch
bouncer to greet the new man, outside off and he leaves alone
tidy start, gentle spin away Collingwood defends
this time Collingwood turns it into the leg side to bring Pietersen on to strike
Pietersen has to stretch forward first ball, that thigh will get a severe working over
gets into a good position here, stretching forward and driving crisply to cover

gone! Maybe that thigh won't get much of a testing then. It was short and slightly wide, Pietersen went back to cut but ends up with a bottom edge on to his foot which goes on to the stumps leaving England in a bit of a mess
Wright defends with an inside edge
touch short, Collingwood aims to cut, but can't find any timing
much fuller this time, Collingwood pops forward to drive, but it skews off the inside half of the bat
hint of width this time, Collingwood tries to guide it to third man, but can't beat point
Hopes doing a fine job here, Collingwood can't beat the infield
once again nothing on offer for Collingwood, he defends quietly
back of a length to finish, Collingwood defends
men at silly mid-off and slip, and so a huge gap at extra cover which Wright finds with a cracking drive. But there is a deep cover, and he cuts if off
driven to mid-off
full and flighted, Collingwood lunges forward to defend
very optimistic appeal from 'keeper and bowler as the ball strikes pad, but there was a massive inside edge on that
slashed but straight to backward point
punched out to deep cover for the single
Collingwood picks up a swift single pushing this full ball to mid on
short and wide, feeding Wright's most comfortable stroke - the off side slash - but there is a deep point in place
suddenly this has a darkly familiar feeling for England, Australia dominant, Collingwood digging desperately
good save this, driven firmly but Hussey dives at short extra
gets this away though, pushing through point for a couple
fuller from Hopes and Collingwood's drive can't pierce the infield
big innings this for Wright, he hasn't batted well this series and has plenty of time to do so here, blocks this studiously off the front foot
picks out a single here, full-facing into the cover region
nicely milked down the ground by Collingwood
Wright is once again forward and defending. Even Tim Paine, the man with the world's most gentle face, seems to be having a fearful sledge
Wright is carefully forward and blocking
slashed hard into the point region, the pace is taken off by a fielder so it's only one
Wright is doing his best Test batting impression, presenting a pendulum-straight bat
this time Wright is defending off the back foot, and doing it very solidly
Hopes is doing a great job, giving nothing away, Wright blocks
England aren't really going anywhere here, this time it's short, Wright is back trying to find a big hook shot, but it top-edges meekly, one-bounce to fine leg
Collingwood is happy to push a single down the ground
better from Wright, solidly forward but pushing past the bowler to milk one
"bowled Stevie," says Tim Paine, and it was, flighted and drawing a forward defence
single here nudged into the leg side
Collingwood gets forward and pushes through extra cover
nothing on offer here, classic defence from Collingwood
nice played, skipping down the track and clipped away for a single in front of midwicket
calmly pushed down the ground for a single
not much happening for the batsmen, maybe they should think about using the Powerplay, it worked wonders for Australia
touch of width allows Wright to slap it through point but there is a fielder set deep
neatly blocked back to the bowler
ooh, big edge on this, but it was a slower ball and bounced a couple of times through to Paine
Collingwood drives crisply but again finds a leaping and diving Hussey
single to finish the over, pushed towards mid on
easy pickings for Collingwood, pace on the ball, angled into the legs, Collingwood clips through straight midwicket for four
cranking up his pace a bit already, Collingwood aims a cut and it's through him before he can lay bat on ball
touch shorter and enough width outside off, left well alone
a play and a miss, full and asking for a drive, Collingwood answers the call but can't connect
it's a quieter start from Tait, the match tension has gone slightly, he bowled a four-over spell first up which may have tired him, still fairly rapid though
Collingwood has fifty! Not sure how much he knew about it, banged in short from Tait, Collingwood on the hook, flies off a top edge all the way over the fine leg boundary
big appeal from Hopes, though it was a touch, err, optimistic from him, thudding into the pads but heading down leg
feeding Wright's cut shot, and it's played very well, but straight to the fielder at point
pressure building on Wright, just finding the fielders a touch
that'll help, again, not quite as planned, big pull shot aimed but it gets a top edge and sails over Paine for four
this is excellently played by Wright, really good shot, couple of steps down the wicket, gave himself a bit of room , but didn't try to overhit his cover drive, instead timing it nicely for a couple
bouncer to finish the over, Wright crouches under it
he's been fearful so far today, but this time Tait dishes up a cuddly leg-stump slower-ball full toss that Collingwood clips for four round the corner
touch short and a touch wide, Collingwood cuts firmly, but deep point keeps it to one
he may not have the rhythm of his earlier spell, but still a decent pace being generated, Wright bottom-edges his attempted cut
good ball this, fuller and straighter and Wright defends
Tait is probably a little fortunate this wasn't called a wide, arrowed down the leg side
full outside off stump, Wright drives through the covers for a couple
nicely done from Collingwood, doing an excellent Hussey impression by dinking it gently behind square on the leg side to run a couple
another leg-side nurdle here, tickled round the corner for one
Wright meets a straight ball with a straighter bat
Wright edges down the wicket, looking to manufacture something but Hopes is far too straight
back of a length and Wright blocks firmly to point
this will be frustrating for Wright, he skipped down the wicket and thumped Hopes straight to the mid off fielder
nicely bowled here, flighted and landing around leg stump, Collingwood blocks
Collingwood was down the track and missed an attempted leg-side clip Tim Paine tried to run round and flick it on to the stumps, missed and allowed an overthrow
Wright gets a single, sweeping carefully
massive appeal as Collingwood played back right in front of his stumps, the ball thudded into the pads but there was  a faint inside edge
no alarm this time, just carefully picked though midwicket for one
Wright is forward and defending a touch uneasily
nicely ticked over by Collingwood here, clipping Hopes to leg gently enough to take a couple
nothing on offer here, defended to midwicket
this is a help-your-self single, pushed down the ground for one
Hopes slips in a bouncer, Wright ducks underneath it
Wright backs away a fraction and guides a drive through point for a quiet single
that'll do for Collingwood, pushing into a space at midwicket and running through for another single
tapped down to long-on for one

Wright slogs sweeps and makes a good connection ... but Shaun Marsh charges round at deep midwicket to take his second superb running catch in the deep. He held this one much more cleanly, and as Smith picks up his second wicket you've got to be thinking this might be it for England.
decent flight and turn from middle and leg, Collingwood stretches forward and defends to the leg side
pulled down too short but Collingwood can't capitalise, chopping straight to extra cover
punched to that man at extra cover once again
straight-driven hard, but straight back to the bowler
slapped to backward point, where the fielder makes a tumbling stop but can't cut off the single, and Bresnan is off the mark
Colly aims a paddle-pull. Ball strikes glove, but goes into space at short fine leg, and they scamper through again
genuine outside edge, flies wide of Paine - dropping infront of him too - and rolls down to third man. That was the slower legcutter from Hopes, and gripped quite nicely in the turf
short ball from Hopes, Bresnan pulls but rolls his wrists on the shot to keep it down as he sends the ball out to deep midwicket
Collingwood moves back and across and jabs to mid-off
too straight, and getting straighter with some movement off the seam, and Collingwood clips out to midwicket
tossed up invitingly, Collingwood takes a couple of steps down the track and sends the ball down to long-on
slightly slower through the air on off stump, Bresnan defends
slips out the side of the hand and goes down the leg side, wide called
tapped softly into the covers
Bresnan stays deep in the crease and tries to steer the ball away square, but point scampers round to cut it off
good shot as Bresnan backs away and carves infront of point, but a superb effort from Bollinger on the ropes saves a boundary
chipped just over and slightly wide of Hussey at straight midwicket, long-on runs round to cut the ball off
driven on the up through the covers
tapped back down the wicket
driven to long-off this time, easy runs for England
yeah, not too sure about this, Hussey drops short and Bresnan has no trouble rocking back and thumping a pull behind square to bring up the 150
and of course, just as I say that Hussey finds the edge of the bat. Thick edge though, and Paine is up to the stumps so no chance to take it
flung well wide of the stumps, that's a huge wide
tapped easily down to long-on
Smith gives the ball a good twirl and lands it on middle and leg, Collingwood lunges out to defend
Colly dances down the track but can't get to the pitch and so defends
solid forward defensive stroke again
nudged out behind square on the leg side, it wasn't hit too hard and was right between the men out there and so they scamper back for the second
a gift - full toss on leg stump - and Collingwood collects a boundary at wide midwicket with a bottom-handed shovel
driven straight to Ponting at cover
low full toss outside off cracked down to long-off
the gentlest of long-hops is dished up outside off and Collingwood gleefully hammers the ball through cover for four
four more! Half-volley and Collingwood gets forward and across to hammer a cover drive through the gap at cover. Great shot, right out the middle, and the Hussey experiment really isn't working
pushed to long-off
and again, by Bresnan this time, and another easy single
driven firmly on the up, but this time straight to the man on the edge of the circle at cover
back of a length, chopped out to deep cover
sliced four for Bresnan! The ball was short and wide and the cut was on, he found good placement and though Hopes slid across at the boundary he couldn't quite cut it off
punched back to the bowler
Bresnan picks up a single to third man
Collingwood goes back and across to a back-of-a-length ball and defends to off
slower cutter, on a length and pushed back to the bowler
pushed straight to point off the back foot
and again, accurate stuff from Harris and Bresnan finds the man at point once more
full this time, and firmly driven by Bresnan but straight to mid-off
Harris errs in line, slipping a length ball down leg, but Bresnan can't get it away and ball strikes the thigh pad
resounding crack off the bat as Bresnan muscles a backfoot drive out to deep cover! And that's the fifty partnership!
flapped to mid-on
Bresnan is struck on the pad and Bollinger launches a huge appeal, but that pitched outside leg and was slipping even further down leg

pulled out to deep midwicket, there's some confusion in the running as Bresnan turns and sets off for the second with Collingwood motionless at the other end. But the throw goes to the wrong end, and he makes it home
chopped down close in on the off side, they think about stealing a single but Bollinger charges across to collect the ball
driven to a deep-ish mid-off, they scamper a single
huge, airy swipe outside off, and Bresnan is lucky not to get an edge on that
half-volley wide of off but Bresnan can't make anything of it, driving straight to mid-off. The fielder was deep, but he hit it too hard to allow a single
nudged to midwicket, and they set off for a single
what a shot! Bresnan hammers a drive up and over cover, and gets four! It wasn't a half-volley by any means, but he absolutely hammered that
clipped infront of square on the leg side
pushed down to long-on
low full toss driven hard to long-off
chopped hard into the ground infront of square, they scamper a single
ooh, he looks a bit stiff, unleashed a massive grunt as he delivered into Collingwood's pads
touch of reverse for Tait, spearing it in full from wide of the crease, Collingwood bunts it for a single to midwicket
Bresnan has the eager look of a man stretching beyond his competence, doing very well here and blocks Tait carefully into the off side

Ponting strikes! Brilliant from the Australian captain! Bresnan pushed towards him and set off for one, Ponting collected, spun and threw at the non-striker's end, direct hit has Bresnan miles short. Big strike that, should settle the game
back of a length and cut firmly to point
over and out! Tait strikes! Stumps clattered! Collingwood advanced down the track, bit of inswing beats the batsman and uproots the leg stump. Defiant knock from Collingwood, but all over now.
Swann off the mark, tickling a sweep round the corner for a couple
nicely played by Swann, touch of width allows a neat back-cut, beating short third man and running away for a couple
haha, well, Swann lined up for a switch hit very early, no Smith shoved down a bouncer, which beat Swann and he almost ended up stumped
less incident here, just driven firmly down the ground for a single
Broad stretches forward and defends carefully
touch fuller from Smith, Broad leans forward, works a single to midwicket to bring up the 200
Broad looks a world of uncertainty at the crease these days, backing away, edging into line and fencing at a ball outside off stump
once again Broad backs away a fraction, Tait fires in a yorker and Broad manages to jab a bat down just in time
once again Broad gives himself room and then ends up with a distinctly tailender looking prod into the cover region for one
ooh, this only missed by a fraction, it was full, very fast and swinging in late to Swann, narrowly missing off stump
Swann more comfortable here, nudging to square leg for a single
great stuff from Tait, this was banged in short and climbed, honing into Broad's face, he managed to get a bat in the way just in time
Swann is forward and pushing a couple towards long on
nicely bowled, a touch slower and loopier, Swann played a sweep but missed
bunted into the leg side again for a couple in front of square, neatly played
excellent shot this, Swann switched hands very early and nailed the hit through what became midwicket, really top shot
touch shorter and allows Swann to get back and cut firmly, picks up two more to deep point
and again! Quality switch-hit this, picking the gap in front of deep cover and timing the shot superbly
Broad doesn't quite manage one of his handsome off-side drives and instead gets an mistimed single
very nicely done from Swann, was a gentle delivery, full toss, but Swann moved across his stumps and clipped it past the short fine leg for four
nicely bowled from Harris, Swann was backing away looking for a shot over cover, Harris followed him and cramped him entirely
four more! Swann picked the slower ball, waited and waited and then swung in between mid on and midwicket for four
and again! Swann still believes, and why not!? Full toss crashed straight back over the bowler's head for four more
nothing here for Swann, he backed away but Harris was good at following him and landing it full, cramping any room and Swann couldn't connect
Duggie has done it! Terrific caught and bowled! Broad mistimed a check-drive back down the wicket, Bollinger stuck out a hand and found the ball in it! That should finally settle this game
Anderson needs a single, but won't find one here, yorker and dug out back to the bowler
short and wide, Anderson flapped an upper-cut down one-bounce to Harris at third man. Swann back on strike
Swann shuffled down the wicket and outside leg, Bollinger shoved it in short and followed him, in the end Swann could only wheel a pull shot away for one to fine leg
Anderson this time finds his a boundary, which is fairly unlikely, it was a full toss, Anderson gave himself some room and landed a rather stylish drive through the covers for four
short and Anderson was looking to find an upper-cut but it whistled past him
Swann has Tait to deal with, who bangs in a short ball, Swann had backed away outside leg and missed his swipe
touch too swift for Swann that, banged in short and zipping past Swann's neck as the batsman tried to swish it away

that'll be all! Tait finishes it off, which is apt, with a slower ball, which isn't! Swann backed away and tried to carve it over mid off but he couldn't time it and ended up gifting a catch to mid off.
